com.kaiserware.sailingrace

Class Fragment_DisplayGoogleMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.app.Fragment
      • com.kaiserware.sailingrace.Fragment_DisplayGoogleMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, com.google.android.gms.maps.OnMapReadyCallback

    public class Fragment_DisplayGoogleMap
extends android.app.Fragment
implements com.google.android.gms.maps.OnMapReadyCallback
    This helper Class is used by: 1) "Activity_StartSequence" (Fragment_StartSequence) to set the windward mark by dragging a marker from the current boat location to some other position and to display the Startline, Boat Heading and the Time / Distance to line and time to burn. 2) "Activity_RaceInfo" (Fragment_RaceInfo) to display the current race course, best tack, and laylines All angles are assumed to be True North for all computations within this App. All UI directions will be displayed as Magnetic North using the GPS declination to convert from True North to Magnetic North. Created by Volker Petersen on November 2015.

      • onMapReady

        public void onMapReady(com.google.android.gms.maps.GoogleMap map)
        Manipulates the map once it has been loaded from the web. This callback is triggered when the map is ready to be used. This is where we can add markers or lines, add listeners or move the camera. If Google Play services is not installed on the device, the user will be prompted to install it inside the SupportMapFragment. This method will only be triggered once the user has installed Google Play services and returned to the app.
        Specified by:
        onMapReady in interface com.google.android.gms.maps.OnMapReadyCallback
